@frankritchie I think our tendency to create meaning when there often isn't any is fairly apparent. 

Life's meaning will never be universal, instead we get to define it for ourselves (in a somewhat deterministic way by the context we exist in).

For me, eudaimonia is the goal.

@TomBagatelle @AutSciPerson Yes, but this is the point though? A lot of our experiences are not uniform. 

There's a lack of shame. Lots of us have/had shame responses. 

A people pleasing Autistic person is quite common, and yet absent from representation.

